    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNow that neovim has a new default color scheme and that `termguicolors` is enabled by default, terminal users who did not use `termguicolors` are likely to see wrongly colored padding on the terminal borders when updating.\r\n\r\nFor example, see this alacritty issue https://github.com/alacritty/alacritty/issues/3746\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThere is a plugin that sends the correct escape sequence to fix this: https://github.com/typicode/bg.nvim.\r\n\r\nBut as the defaults have changed, it would make sense to do this in the stock configuration.",
